[{"location":"#Introduction","page":"Introduction","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Introduction","title":"Introduction","text":"SelfAvoidingBilliards is a Julia package to simulating the a mathematical billiard with an added memory. This package is largely copied from DynamicalBilliards.jl, please also refer to that documentation for more information.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Introduction","title":"Introduction","text":"This documentation will cover the important differences from the original code, as well as some practical examples on how to use the code.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Introduction","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Introduction","title":"Introduction","text":"Automatically adding walls when bouncing a particle\nReducing the billiard to remove unnessecary walls","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Introduction","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Introduction","title":"Introduction","text":"The package is not (yet) featured on the registry, so for now it can be installed by typing ] add https://github.com/stijndelnoij/SelfAvoidingBilliards in shell mode, or Pkg.add(\"https://github.com/stijndelnoij/SelfAvoidingBilliards\") using Pkg.","category":"page"}]
